FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISS STONES was recalcitrant behind the gate, broke in but was away fast, moved in while going to the front, showed the way with a clear advantage, was asked for more while three then two wide on the turn, extended the advantage into upper stretch, drew off under a solid hand-ride into the final furlong and proved much the best with her ears pricked under light coaxing to the finish. JESSICA'S RIDE bumped soundly with a foe while off a step slow, dropped back while climbing then was taken up some, raced at the rear under urging, went two then three wide around the turn, was driven five wide into the stretch then moved further out and finished willingly to get up for the place. SHORT SHIFT was off slow and spotted the front two a few lengths, raced at the rear under urging, hugged the rail around the turn, drafted behind foes late on that bend, got through along the rail into the stretch then moved out at the three-sixteenths and missed the place while clear for the show. PHOTON was away alertly, angled out early then chased the pace, went four then three wide early on the turn, shifted five wide near the five-sixteenths, turned into upper stretch under the crop and tired. BON ADIEU was restless in the gate, broke a step slow then moved out early before being corrected, raced just off the pace, chased in the two path around the turn, was bumped nearing the quarter-pole and capitulated. SHE'S A NINE bumped soundly with a rival at the start then was taken up a bit while off a bit slow, moved up on the outside under urging then chased the pace, went five then four wide around the turn, lugged in late on that bend then bumped with a foe near the quarter-pole, lugged in outside of a foe while not urged in the stretch and dropped out.

OUR ROSIE DIAMONDS was urged along on the outside, went five wide around the turn, came seven wide into the stretch and lacked the needed response. JET SET JULIET contested the pace on the outside of two opponents, vied in the three path on the turn and came up empty. FULIGNI was hustled from the gate, contested the pace on the inside of a duo, vied along the rail on the turn, dropped back into upper stretch and tired. BEN'S SUNNY ISLAND disputed the pace between horses, vied in the two path on the turn, dropped back into upper stretch and weakened. PREDETERMINED was off slow then dropped well behind, moved from the three path to the rail early on the turn, saved ground from that point into the stretch and was no factor. AUDIT COMMITTEE left the gate under urging, was taken up while shut-off near the nine-sixteenths then clipped heels and stumbled, dropped back quickly while trying to recover, went four wide around the turn, came five wide into the stretch and had nothing left.
